36#include "kuser_locl.h"
37#include "heimtools-commands.h"
38
39#ifdef HAVE_READLINE
40char *readline(const char *prompt);
41#else
42
43static char *
44readline(const char *prompt)
45{
46 char buf[BUFSIZ];
47 printf ("%s", prompt);
48 fflush (stdout);
49 if(fgets(buf, sizeof(buf), stdin) == NULL)
50 return NULL;
51 buf[strcspn(buf, "\r\n")] = '\0';
52 return strdup(buf);
53}
54
55#endif
56
57/*
58 *
59 */
60
61int
62kswitch(struct kswitch_options *opt, int argc, char **argv)
63{
64 krb5_error_code ret;
65 krb5_ccache id = NULL;
66
67 if (opt->cache_string && opt->principal_string)
68 krb5_errx(heimtools_context, 1,
69 N_("Both --cache and --principal given, choose one", ""));
70
71 if (opt->interactive_flag) {
72 krb5_cc_cache_cursor cursor;
73 krb5_ccache *ids = NULL;
74 size_t i, len = 0;
75 char *name;
76 rtbl_t ct;
77
78 ct = rtbl_create();
79
80 rtbl_add_column_by_id(ct, 0, "#", 0);
81 rtbl_add_column_by_id(ct, 1, "Principal", 0);
82 rtbl_set_column_affix_by_id(ct, 1, " ", "");
83 rtbl_add_column_by_id(ct, 2, "Type", 0);
84 rtbl_set_column_affix_by_id(ct, 2, " ", "");
85
86 ret = krb5_cc_cache_get_first(heimtools_context, NULL, &cursor);
87 if (ret)
88 krb5_err(heimtools_context, 1, ret, "krb5_cc_cache_get_first");
89
90 while (krb5_cc_cache_next(heimtools_context, cursor, &id) == 0) {
91 krb5_principal p;
92 char num[10];
93
94 ret = krb5_cc_get_principal(heimtools_context, id, &p);
95 if (ret) {
96 krb5_cc_close(heimtools_context, id);
97 continue;
98 }
99
100 ret = krb5_unparse_name(heimtools_context, p, &name);
101 krb5_free_principal(heimtools_context, p);
102
103 snprintf(num, sizeof(num), "%d", (int)(len + 1));
104 rtbl_add_column_entry_by_id(ct, 0, num);
105 rtbl_add_column_entry_by_id(ct, 1, name);
106 rtbl_add_column_entry_by_id(ct, 2, krb5_cc_get_type(heimtools_context, id));
107 free(name);
108
109 ids = erealloc(ids, (len + 1) * sizeof(ids[0]));
110 ids[len] = id;
111 len++;
112 }
113 krb5_cc_cache_end_seq_get(heimtools_context, cursor);
114
115 rtbl_format(ct, stdout);
116 rtbl_destroy(ct);
117
118 name = readline("Select number: ");
119 if (name) {
120 i = atoi(name);
121 if (i == 0)
122 krb5_errx(heimtools_context, 1, "Cache number '%s' is invalid", name);
123 if (i > len)
124 krb5_errx(heimtools_context, 1, "Cache number '%s' is too large", name);
125
126 id = ids[i - 1];
127 ids[i - 1] = NULL;
128 free(name);
129 } else
130 krb5_errx(heimtools_context, 1, "No cache selected");
131 for (i = 0; i < len; i++)
132 if (ids[i])
133 krb5_cc_close(heimtools_context, ids[i]);
134 free(ids);
135 } else if (opt->principal_string) {
136 krb5_principal p;
137
138 ret = krb5_parse_name(heimtools_context, opt->principal_string, &p);
139 if (ret)
140 krb5_err(heimtools_context, 1, ret, "krb5_parse_name: %s",
141 opt->principal_string);
142
143 ret = krb5_cc_cache_match(heimtools_context, p, &id);
144 if (ret)
145 krb5_err(heimtools_context, 1, ret,
146 N_("Did not find principal: %s", ""),
147 opt->principal_string);
148
149 krb5_free_principal(heimtools_context, p);
150
151 } else if (opt->cache_string) {
152 const krb5_cc_ops *ops;
153 char *str;
154 int aret;
155
156 ops = krb5_cc_get_prefix_ops(heimtools_context, opt->type_string);
157 if (ops == NULL)
158 krb5_err(heimtools_context, 1, 0, "krb5_cc_get_prefix_ops");
159
160 aret = asprintf(&str, "%s:%s", ops->prefix, opt->cache_string);
161 if (aret == -1)
162 krb5_errx(heimtools_context, 1, N_("out of memory", ""));
163
164 ret = krb5_cc_resolve(heimtools_context, str, &id);
165 if (ret)
166 krb5_err(heimtools_context, 1, ret, "krb5_cc_resolve: %s", str);
167
168 free(str);
169 } else {
170 krb5_errx(heimtools_context, 1, "missing option for kswitch");
171 }
172
173 ret = krb5_cc_switch(heimtools_context, id);
174 if (ret)
175 krb5_err(heimtools_context, 1, ret, "krb5_cc_switch");
176
177 krb5_cc_close(heimtools_context, id);
178
179 return 0;
180}
